Sascoc has continued its offensive against Sports Minister Nathi Mthethwa's involvement at Cricket South Africa. The Olympic body is questioning whether Mthethwa flouted the National Sport and Recreation Act in his involvement in the adoption of a new board at CSA. eNCA's Hloni Mtimkulu has more. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Sascoc has continued its offensive against the Sports Minister's involvement at Cricket South Africa. The Olympic body is questioning whether Minister Nathi Mthethwa flouted the National Sport and Recreation Act in his involvement in the adoption of a new board at CSA. READ: Mthethwa withdraws section 13 notice against CSA Sascoc is asking the Sports Portfolio Committee to investigate the minister's actions. Mthethwa is accused of forcing Cricket SA into a Memorandum of Incorporation (MOI). Sascoc has rejected the MOI that was agreed on 27 April by the CSA's interim board and members' council.